ğŸ§  What is a Functional Component?

A **functional component** is a **JavaScript function** that **returns JSX (UI)**.

```jsx
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello React</h1>;
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Components must start with a **capital letter**
ğŸ“Œ Return **one parent element**

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š Functional vs Class Components

| Functional         | Class                  |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Simple JS function | ES6 class              |
| Uses Hooks         | Uses lifecycle methods |
| Less code          | More boilerplate       |
| Preferred â­        | Legacy                 |

ğŸ“Œ **Modern React uses Functional Components**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Basic Functional Component Example

```jsx
function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>My First React App</h1>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© JSX Rules (Quick Recap)

* Must return **one parent**
* Use `className` instead of `class`
* JS inside `{ }`

```jsx
<h1 className="title">{name}</h1>
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“¦ Using Props in Functional Components

**Props** are used to **pass data to components**.

```jsx
function User(props) {
  return <h2>Hello {props.name}</h2>;
}

<User name="Saakshi" />
```

ğŸ“Œ Props are **read-only**

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âœ¨ Props with Destructuring (Best Practice)

```jsx
function User({ name, age }) {
  return <p>{name} - {age}</p>;
}
```

âœ” Cleaner
âœ” Readable

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Reusing Functional Components

```jsx
<User name="A" />
<User name="B" />
<User name="C" />
```

ğŸ“Œ Same component, different data

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Introducing Hooks (Preview)

Hooks allow **state & features** in functional components.

Example:

```jsx
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      Count: {count}
    </button>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Hooks work **only in functional components**

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”„ Rendering Flow

1. Component function runs
2. JSX returned
3. Virtual DOM created
4. UI rendered

ğŸ“Œ On state/props change â†’ re-render

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Common Patterns

Conditional Rendering

```jsx
{isLoggedIn && <Dashboard />}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Rendering Lists

```jsx
{items.map(item => (
  <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>
))}
```

ğŸ“Œ Always use **unique key**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Common Beginner Mistakes

* Forgetting `return`
* Using lowercase component names
* Modifying props
* Missing `key` in lists

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

* One component = one responsibility
* Use props destructuring
* Keep components small
* Use functional components by default
* Use hooks correctly

